Package: BayesPsychometric
Type: Package
Title: Fits Psychometric Functions Using Bayesian Methods
Version: 0.4.1
Author: Alex Knudson
Maintainer: Alex Knudson <aknudson@nevada.unr.edu>
Description: A package that is focused on fitting psychometric functions often found in the field of psychology. It provides functionality for estimating categorical effects as well as the point of subjective simultaneity/equality (PSS/PSE), just noticeable difference/intensity (JND/JNI), and multilevel effects.
License: GPLv3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    assertthat,
    purrr
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: 
    rstan
